name: Neptune Swim
description:
”Once, there was an ocean. It stretched out across the world, covering everything. There were boats with sailors on them, ready to discover what mammoth creatures swam in its depths. Children played in the shallows, splashing the water around them with their tiny hands. The waters were always calm and inviting, but soon they became still like stone - like jewels on a beautiful string. For no one knew that the ocean was gone, except for us - the spirits of Neptune's court.” - Sykcolo
